title.rendered: Gujarat vs Chennai, Indian T20 League 2023: Today’s Fantasy Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
Gujarat vs Chennai, Indian T20 League 2023: Fantasy Picks for Today’s Match

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Playing XIs for Gujarat & Chennai

David Miller will miss this clash due to international commitments.

Gujarat: Shubman Gill, Wriddhiman Saha (wk), Kane Williamson*, Hardik Pandya (c), Matthew Wade*, Rahul Tewatia, Ravisrinivasan Sai Kishore, Rashid Khan*, Alzarri Joseph*, Shivam Mavi/Yash Dayal, Mohammed Shami

Maheesh Theekshana and Matheesha Pathirana will be busy playing the white-ball series in New Zealand.

Ben Stokes will play only as a batter for the first few games of the tournament.

Chennai: Ruturaj Gaikwad, Devon Conway*, Moeen Ali*, Ben Stokes*, Ravindra Jadeja, Ambati Rayudu/Shivam Dube, MS Dhoni (c & wk), Dwaine Pretorius*, Deepak Chahar, Simarjeet Singh/Tushar Deshpande, Prashant Solanki

Narendra Modi Stadium, Ahmedabad Pitch Report

Venue: Narendra Modi Stadium, Ahmedabad

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 174

2nd innings average score: 129

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Also Read:

Bangalore vs Mumbai, Indian T20 League 2023: Fantasy Tips

Punjab vs Kolkata Indian T20 League 2023 Fantasy Tips

LSG vs Delhi Indian T20 League 2023 Fantasy Tips

Hyderabad vs Rajasthan, Indian T20 League 2023 Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Shubman Gill and Hardik Pandya have enjoyed playing at the Narendra Modi Stadium. While Gill averages a whopping 112 including the highest score of 126*, Pandya averages 30 with the bat and has taken 10 wickets including the best figures of four for 16.

Ravisrinivasan Sai Kishore starred in the Best11 in last year’s final, taking two wickets and as many catches. Above all, he generates bonus points with his disciplined bowling, giving away runs at an economy of 5.4 in 49 T20s.

Gujarat couldn’t trouble Ruturaj Gaikwad in 2022. He registered scores of 53 and 72.

Wriddhiman Saha collected 78 runs and took two catches in two outings against Chennai in the last edition. In fact, he was impactful throughout the season: 317 runs at 32 and 13 dismissals (second-highest).

The last time Ben Stokes played with MS Dhoni in the Indian T20 League, he accumulated 316 runs at 32 and picked 12 wickets.

Devon Conway averages an impressive 35 in 16 professional T20s in the subcontinent.

Over the past three editions, MS Dhoni’s average with the bat has dropped to 18. However, he has made amends by inflicting as many as 38 dismissals.

By striking regularly with new and old ball, Mohammed Shami took 19 or more wickets in each of the last four seasons.

Rashid Khan has picked 17 wickets in his last 10 professional T20s and has now bowled 100 consecutive deliveries without conceding a boundary in T20Is.

In the last three games at the venue, 83% of the wickets have belonged to seamers.

Are you ready? Make your winning team on My11Circle Fantasy Cricket App now!
